EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; REWARD OFFERED IN EXPOSURE INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Crime Stoppers Program is offering up to $1,000 for 
information that helps identify a man who exposed himself in front of four 
young girls in Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect is described as a 25-year-old, unkempt white male with straight 
brown hair and a white pickup truck. 
</P>
<P>
 He exposed himself to the girls ranging in age from 8 to 16 on Nov. 11 near 
400 Charles St., according to a Crime Stoppers release. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with any information about the crime should call 494-TALK. Callers may 
remain anonymous. 
</P>
<P>
 Callers to the line will be assigned an identification number used to present 
rewards if the information leads to an arrest and a criminal complaint. JAMES 
MAIELLA JR. 
