</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Melissa Gower scored 23 points as Long Beach State rallied to beat Cal State 
Fullerton, 81-76, in a Big West Conference women's basketball game Thursday at 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach trailed, 38-31, at the half but the 49ers outscored the Titans, 
50-38, in the second half.Long Beach State took advantage of Fullerton's 
depleted ranks. The Titans started with eight players but two fouled out and 
another was sidelined because of an injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Marissa Frial scored 18 points and Koko Lahanas added 16 and nine rebounds for 
Fullerton (1-7, 0-2). Long Beach is 2-6, 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Big West Conference game: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara 77, UC Irvine 71 -- UC Santa Barbara held off a late UC 
Irvine rally to defeat the Anteaters in the Big West Conference women's 
basketball opener for both teams. 
</P>
