<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAIDERS GRANTED TICKET EXTENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With only about 54,000 tickets sold for Sunday's wild-card playoff game 
against the Denver Broncos, the Raiders were granted a two-day extension by the 
NFL to sell out the 67,800-seat Coliseum so that the local television blackout 
could be lifted. 
</P>
<P>
 The league gave the Raiders until 1 p.m. Saturday to reach stadium capacity 
because of last weekend's New Year's holiday. The Raiders were also granted 
extra time last week to lift the blackout before their 33-30 victory over the 
Broncos. 
</P>
