<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; USC RALLIES BEHIND ATWATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reserve Tracy Atwater scored 10 of her 15 points in the second half as No. 
10-ranked USC rallied for a 63-56 victory over Oregon State on Thursday night 
at Corvallis, Ore., in the Pacific 10 Conference opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 The Trojans, 8-1 overall and 1-0 in the Pac-10, trailed, 50-41, with 7:55 to 
play, but went on a 22-6 run to clinch the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Leslie had 13 points and 14 rebounds in only 28 minutes as she got into 
early foul trouble. 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon State is 8-3 and 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon 82, UCLA 77 -- The Bruins rallied from a 13-point deficit to get within 
one, but failed to overtake the Ducks at Eugene, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 Natalie Williams led UCLA (5-5, 0-1) with 18 points and Allison Arredondo 
matched a career high with 17 points, including five three-pointers. 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon (7-3, 1-0) was led by Debbie Sporcich with 24 points and 16 rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
