<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CAL STATE NORTHRIDGE GAINS PAIR OF TRANSFERS FOR TRACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 High jumper Criss Moxley from Saddleback College and hurdler Malcolm Stewart 
from Sacramento City College are expected to enroll at Cal State Northridge 
today and will be eligible to compete for the Matador track and field team this 
spring. 
</P>
<P>
 Moxley, a sophomore, has a personal best of 6 feet 11 inches in the high jump. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart, a junior, has run 54.2 seconds in the 400-meter intermediate hurdles, 
but Northridge Coach Don Strametz said he might be redshirted this year, 
depending on his fitness level at the start of the season. Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 A decision on the athletic eligibility of three former Faith Baptist High 
baseball players has again been delayed by a City Section committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Seniors Chad Evanson, Mike Jimenez and Clint Marcus left Faith Baptist after 
their junior year. Decisions on their financial hardship petitions already have 
been delayed three times. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents of the three players were told by the City athletics office Thursday 
that a decision would not be announced until today because of a backlog of 
agenda items. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm frustrated," Marcus said. "Tryouts are coming up and I want to know what 
I'm going to be doing." 
</P>
<P>
 Marcus transferred to El Camino Real; Evanson and Jimenez are enrolled at 
Chatsworth. Golf 
</P>
<P>
 The GTE West Classic, a 54-hole $550,000 Senior PGA Tour event, begins March 4 
at the Ojai Valley Inn. 
</P>
<P>
 Expected to play are defending champion Al Geiberger as well as Dave Stockton, 
Chi Chi Rodriguez, Arnold Palmer, Bob Murphy, Gary Player, George Archer, Jim 
Dent, Bruce Crampton and Jim Colbert. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-646-5796 or 805-583-8700. Running 
</P>
<P>
 The Roy Campanella Northridge Memorial 5K/10K Run & Walk is scheduled for 
Sunday at Cal State Northridge. Proceeds benefit the Northridge Heart Institute 
at the Northridge Hospital Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The event was renamed this year in honor of Campanella, the Dodgers' Hall of 
Fame catcher and a longtime Valley resident. 
</P>
<P>
 Former Dodger Don Newcombe is honorary host. Registration for the event may be 
made in advance or the day of the race. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-885-5341. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Cliff Floyd, a top prospect with the Montreal Expos as an outfielder and first 
baseman, and Carlos Palomino, former world welterweight champion, will appear 
at a sports card show Saturday from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the Warner Center 
Hilton in Woodland Hills. 
</P>
