<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; POLICE IDENTIFY CRASH VICTIM; MAN HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 63-year-old man killed in a San Diego Freeway collision Wednesday night has 
been identified as Frank Rose Jr. of Garden Grove, the California Highway 
Patrol said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rose was driving south just north of the Seal Beach Boulevard off-ramp when 
his car was hit by a van being driven by a suspected drunk driver, according to 
CHP Officer Denise Quesada. 
</P>
<P>
 "The impact of the accident was so severe that the man's car spun out of 
control and was basically cut in half," Quesada said. 
</P>
<P>
 An off-duty Long Beach firefighter who was passing by just after the accident 
pulled Rose from the car and began performing cardiopulmonary resuscitation 
until paramedics arrived. Rose died at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the van, 49-year-old James Edward Kruger of Garden Grove, 
suffered minor injuries in the crash and was treated at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 He was later arrested on suspicion of drunk driving and taken to Orange County 
Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone who may have witnessed the accident is asked to call the CHP's 
Westminster office at (714) 892-4426. GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
