(Tokyo String Quartet) (RCA Victor Red Seal). Tippett: "Byzantium" -- Michael 
Tippett, composer (Sir Georg Solti, conductor, Chicago Symphony; Faye Robinson, 
soprano) (London). 
</P>
<P>
 * Best Engineered Recording, Classical: Adams: "The Death of Klinghoffer" -- 
(Kent Nagano, conductor, Orchestra of the Opera de Lyon); Henk Jansen, engineer 
(Elektra Nonesuch). Bartok: "The Wooden Prince" and "Cantata Profana" -- 
