 Judge Rules in Hendrix Case: A federal district judge in Seattle ruled that 
MCA Music Entertainment cannot move ahead with its planned multimillion-dollar 
purchase of Jimi Hendrix's recording and publishing copyrights until a lawsuit 
filed by the late rock star's father is resolved. The 8-month-old fraud 
litigation, which does not name MCA as a defendant, accuses Los Angeles 
entertainment attorney Leo Branton and several corporations of selling the 
rights to the psychedelic guitarist's catalogue without the knowledge or 
consent of the father, James (Al) Hendrix. 
