<P>
 Arco Sues ARB Over Diesel Fuel Enforcement: Atlantic Richfield Co. filed suit 
in Los Angeles County Superior Court against the state Air Resources Board for 
failure to enforce its own clean-diesel fuel rule, which took effect Oct. 1. In 
August, fearing shortages of the new fuel -- designed to reduce emissions of 
soot-like particles and other pollutants -- the board extended the deadline for 
Chevron Corp., Unocal Corp. and Ultramar Inc. to produce the cleaner fuel.Arco 
had already invested $70 million to modify its Los Angeles refinery to make the 
new fuel and met the deadline. Arco called the ARB decision a "capricious 
relaxation" of the rule, first issued in 1988, and has sued in part to stop any 
further extensions to other refiners. 
