<P>
 Rates Rise On 52-Week Treasury Bills: Interest rates on the bills rose at 
auction to the highest level in 13 months.The average discount rate was 3.52%, 
up from 3.47% at the last auction Dec. 9. It was the highest rate since 52-week 
bills averaged 3.57% on Dec. 10, 1992. The bills will carry an equivalent 
coupon interest rate of 3.67%, with each $10,000 in face value selling for 
$9,644.10. Sales totaled $16 billion out of bids of $63 billion. 
