<TEXT>
<P>
 Mortgage Rates Rise: The average interest rate on 30-year, fixed-rate 
mortgages rose to 7.23% this week, the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. 
said.The average was up from 7.13% the previous week but still below 7.31% at 
the end of November. The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% in October, but it 
has been above 7% for the last 10 weeks. On one-year, adjustable-rate 
mortgages, lenders were asking an average initial rate of 4.23%, up from 4.20% 
last week. Fifteen-year notes, an increasingly popular option for people 
refinancing their mortgages, averaged 6.74% this week, up from 6.63% a week 
earlier. The rates do not include add-on fees known as points. 
</P>
