<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Animation: Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc. is establishing a new in-house animation 
group to develop television and film projects as part of the Santa Monica 
studio's revived MGM/UA Television unit.The animation unit is expected to 
develop projects related to characters in the company's film library, including 
the Pink Panther. Executive Vice President Don Mirisch, a former Hanna-Barbera 
executive, will oversee MGM Animation. Two other former Hanna-Barbera 
executives, Paul Sabella and Mark Young, will serve as vice presidents, along 
with former MCA Family Entertainment executive Kelly Ward and former DIC 
executive Jonathan Dern. 
</P>
