<P>
THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX: STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended Jan. 2, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold: Latest 
Week Albums: 19.2 Singles: 2.7 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago Albums: 31.8 Singles: 3.2 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago Albums: 17.7 Singles: 2.5 
</P>
<P>
 HITS MAGAZINE TIP OF THE WEEK 
</P>
<P>
 The very profitable annual Lollapalooza tour is shaping up with insiders 
saying Nirvana, Smashing Pumpkins and the Beastie Boys have already been 
confirmed. Meanwhile, Lollapalooza founder (and Porno for Pyros leader) Perry 
Farrell has split with manager Ted Gardner, who is also one of the organizers 
of Lollapalooza.Industry chatter has the split occurring because Farrell wanted 
Porno for Pyros to headline Lollapalooza '94. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Hits magazine is a weekly music industry trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
 Sources: Soundscan Inc.; Billboard magazine 
</P>
</TEXT>
