</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Craig McCallum Named President of Mission Viejo Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * Craig McCallum has been appointed president and chief operating officer of 
Mission Viejo Co. 
</P>
<P>
 As president, McCallum, 48, will be responsible for all commercial and 
residential development in planned communities such as 10,000-acre Mission 
Viejo and 6,600-acre Aliso Viejo and the 22,000-acre Highlands Ranch project in 
Colorado, said James G. Gilleran, chief executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Most recently, McCallum was president of Mission Viejo Co.'s Colorado 
division. His affiliation with the development company began in 1973, when he 
was a planner with the engineering firm of Raub, Bein Frost and Associates, a 
portion of which was acquired by Mission Viejo Co. Before that, he worked in 
the planning department of Irvine Co. 
</P>
<P>
 With 8,600 homes and 19,000 residents now, Aliso Viejo is expected to have 
20,000 units and 48,000 residents when completed in 2005, a company spokeswoman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mission Viejo planned community now has 26,500 units and 75,700 residents, 
she said, and is expected to have about 30,400 dwelling units for a population 
of about 90,000 when it completes its 30-year plan in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
