 He was taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital, where he died from 
massive internal injuries later in the day, authorities said. Carolyn Lucas, 
33, of Lancaster, the driver of the second car, suffered injuries in the 
collision. She was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills, where 
she remains listed in stable condition, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
