<TEXT>
<P>
 Three male youths were arrested Thursday on suspicion of burglary and 
vandalism of a children's group home that was rendered uninhabitable by an 
attack that did an estimated $2,800 damage to the structure, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects, all from Acton, allegedly entered a group home in the 32800 
block of Crown Valley Road sometime between Dec. 26 and 28, when the residents 
were away on an outing, authorities said. 
