<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 2 BODIES FOUND IN RAVINE ARE IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities have identified the two dead men found in the rural area of Canyon 
Country last week as Los Angeles residents. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Lee Chambers, 36, and Warren Jenkins, 31, were discovered Dec. 29 in a 
ravine near Soledad Canyon and Capra roads by a jogger who detected a foul odor 
in the area, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy Irma Becerra. 
</P>
<P>
 Chambers had been shot in the head and both arms and stabbed in the upper 
body, and Jenkins had been shot and stabbed in the upper body. 
</P>
<P>
 Both men are believed to have been dead for several days before they were 
found about five miles east of Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators discovered a sandwich bag containing more than an ounce of rock 
cocaine on one body, but are unsure if the killings were drug-related. The 
plastic bag was concealed in the man's underwear. 
</P>
<P>
 No shell casings were found at the scene, leading investigators to believe the 
attacks occurred elsewhere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
